ts interpretation in Judaism and Christianity.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 17. Dez 2021) 4aAntikes Judentum. 4aBen Sira. 4aDeuterokanonische Schriften. 4aSirach. 4aTextgeschichte. 7aRELIGION / Judaism / General.2bisacsh  aAncient Judaism.  aBen Sira.  aDeuterocanonical Books.  aSirach.  aTextual History.1 aKreuzer, Siegfried.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET THEOLOGIE, RELIGIONSWISS., JUDAISTIK  2013z9783110317336oZDB-23-DGF0 cprintz978311030032140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311030051240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110300512423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110300512/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_CL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-DGFb2013  aZDB-23-DGGb2013  aZDB-23-GTRc2000d2014